ted most likely in an access area making way towards the Barbaricum from the Empire and vice versa, represented by \"Valley Sălăuţei\" research assumes that we are dealing perhaps with a burgus-like structure.Due to the proximity of the burgus of Salva to the auxiliary camp of Ilişua - Arcobadara  (adjoined by a similar military structure set in  neighboring Negrilești)  it can be said that these burgus seems to adhere to the administrative territory named territorium Arcobadarense.','pasune','c. 106 - 270',NULL,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1864 a toponymic survey carried out by Gubern of  Transylvania mentioned a structure and abundance of archaeological material at Salva','','It is in a constant process of destruction due to agricultural works',NULL,'brittaburkhardt@gmail.com','2018-05-25 15:42:52','2018-05-28 09:52:33','RO048','Proposal for classification','34404','Private','Unidentified','','25110','',NULL,'Plateau ','Sălăuţei valley','-','(2002) Retegan','agricultural plots','Tănase Todoran street','road','agricultural plots','',NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','','','5','',NULL,'2016','-','MNIT','ceramics and stone and brick material',1,NULL,'','','','5',''),(24,'Poieni','Bologa',7,NULL,'Ruconium - Bologa','Grădiște','Romania',NULL,'','CJ-I-s-A-06975','',NULL,'160m / 235m / 213m','125 m / 125 m / 133 m','529 m ','','presupuse',' 27946 square metre','The fort is located on a plateau, at the eastern outskirts of the village, south/south-east of the confluence of the Săcuieu or Henţu rivers (west of the castrum) and Crişul Repede (flowing  east and north of the fort). In the 1970s the praetorium was identified on the right-hand side of the commanders building. The master\'s building occupies an area of 570 square meters.\r\nStamped tiles have been discovered on which a fragment of a stamp belonging to the Hispanorum cohors II and several fragments of the Aelia Gaesatorum cohors have been distinguished.\r\nSince then researched identified different phases of the fort,  in which the dimensions and as well as construction material varies.\r\nThe fort has a total of three phases: the first phase (106-125/126; 160x125 m) of wood and earth; the second phase (126/130 - 210; 235x125 m) of wood and earth; and the third phase (210-27;213x133 m) with the fort built of stone.\r\nSeveral internal edifices were identified (principia, praetorium, horreum, barracks and other buildings)  consisting of structure made of wood and / or stone; some of them also have underwent modification during the abovementioned different phases.\r\n','teren_arabil','c. 106 - 270',NULL,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',' national or universal value','The area of the camp is well preserved, clearly defined throughout the perimeter.\r\nInside - as long as they have not been affected by agricultural work, treasure hunters, stone extraction, or even archaeological excavations (especially in the central area) - the remaining structures also appear well preserved (see recent archaeological and geophysical research).',NULL,'brittaburkhardt@gmail.com','2018-05-25 15:56:07','2018-05-28 08:23:37','RO183','59069.01 ','59069','Mixt (Public-Private) Poieni town hall.','Private owners (unknown)','DJ103H, Bologa 407471, Romania','52087','',NULL,'high terrace','Crișul Repede River','3 phases: the first phase (106-125/126 p. C.) of wood and earth; the second phase (126-130 p.C. - 210 BC) of wood and earth; and the third phase (210-270 p.C.) with the fort built of stone.',' (1936) M. Macrea; (1967-1976) E. Chirilă N. Gudea; (2012-2016) F. Marcu ','Crisul Repede river',' Săcuieu (Henţu) river','An imaginary line at 500 m north of the camp connecting the rivers Crisul Repede and Săcuieu (Henţu)','An imaginary line at 500 m north of the camp connecting the rivers Crisul Repede and Săcuieu (Henţu)','',NULL,'','4','','4','4','','','','','4','','5','5','',NULL,'2016','yes','MNIT',' de verificat literatura',1,NULL,'Legea nr. 182/2000 privind protejarea patrimoniului cultural național mobil','','O